说她给国王下了毒 想为她自己夺取王位
That she was bent on taking the throne by herself by poisoning the king.

175
00:26:47,060 --> 00:26:50,900
几周后 国王死了
A few weeks later the king died.

176
00:26:56,500 --> 00:27:00,000
而王子还年轻 不能登基为国王
The prince was too young to take the king's place...

177
00:27:00,170 --> 00:27:06,090
因此根据法律 女王将统治一年
So, by law, the queen would rule for another year.

178
00:27:10,100 --> 00:27:12,770
未来成了未知
The future was uncertain.

179
00:27:24,630 --> 00:27:29,050
期间 王子有了心上人
The prince meanwhile had given away his heart.

180
00:27:29,220 --> 00:27:33,560
她既漂亮又聪明 只是一个农夫的女儿
She was beautiful and smart, and though only a farmer's daughter...

181
00:27:33,730 --> 00:27:36,940
全国都觉得他们很般配
the kingdom smiled on the match.

182
00:27:40,530 --> 00:27:44,790
然而 女王更享受当女王的乐趣
The queen however, was rather enjoying being queen.

183
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:49,130
除了嫁给王子还有什么更好的办法保留王位呢
And what better way to remain so, than to marry the prince herself?

184
00:27:49,300 --> 00:27:51,300
什么 这真恶心
What? That's disgusting.

185
00:27:51,470 --> 00:27:53,970
- 她是他外婆 - 是他继任的外婆
- She was his grandmother. - Step grandmother...

186
00:27:54,140 --> 00:27:57,730
但还是一个年轻漂亮的女人 可别忘了这点
and still a young, beautiful woman herself, don't forget.

187
00:27:57,900 --> 00:28:00,740
王子可不喜欢这主意
The prince, however, didn't like the idea.

188
00:28:05,750 --> 00:28:09,750
他带着农夫的女儿 骑马逃至夜深
He took the farmer's daughter, and they rode away into the night.

189
00:28:12,680 --> 00:28:15,930
他们在紫杉树的树枝下停下休息
They stopped to rest under the branches of a yew tree.

190
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:17,610
那是你
That's you.

191
00:28:18,770 --> 00:28:21,450
第二天早晨 王子醒来
The next morning the Prince awoke.

192
00:28:22,110 --> 00:28:25,280
起来了 我的爱人 他说道
"Arise, my beloved" he said.

193
00:28:25,450 --> 00:28:29,210
但农夫的女儿一动也不动
But the farmer's daughter did not steer...

194
00:28:30,810 --> 00:28:33,620
而王子注意到了血
Which was when the prince noticed the blood.

195
00:28:33,660 --> 00:28:34,590
血?
Blood?

196
00:28:34,590 --> 00:28:37,220
有人在晚上杀了他的爱人
Someone had killed his beloved in the night.

197
00:28:37,220 --> 00:28:38,390
什么
What?

198
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:41,730
女王 他哭泣道
"The Queen" he cried.

199
00:28:41,900 --> 00:28:44,560
女王杀了我的新娘
"The queen has murdered my bride."

200
00:28:45,570 --> 00:28:50,080
村民们满腔怒火 复仇心切 他们暴动了
The villagers, full of fury and vengeance, rose up at the crime.

201
00:28:50,240 --> 00:28:53,330
我就在那时走动了起来
It was then that I came walking.

202
00:29:16,850 --> 00:29:20,130
女王再也没有出现过
The queen was never seen again.

203
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:25,560
很好 她罪有应得
Good. She deserved it.

204
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:29,710
我外婆的事  我想你也帮不上忙
Now, I don't suppose you can help me with my grandma.

205
00:29:30,050 --> 00:29:32,320
故事还没结束
The story is not yet finished.

206
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:36,190
我把女王带到了非常远的地方
I took the queen and carried her far enough away

207
00:29:36,190 --> 00:29:38,980
人们永远不会找到她
so that the townspeople would never find her...

208
00:29:39,100 --> 00:29:42,890
在海边的一个村庄里  她开始了新的生活
to a village by the sea, where she began a new life.

209
00:29:43,500 --> 00:29:45,300
但她杀了农夫的女儿
But she killed the farmer's daughter.

210
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,960
你怎么能救一个杀人犯
How can you save a murderer?

211
00:29:48,850 --> 00:29:50,200
你真的是一个怪物
You really are a monster.

212
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:52,730
我从没说是她杀了农夫的女儿
I never said she killed farmer's daughter.

213
00:29:52,980 --> 00:29:56,590
我只说过王子那么说的
I only said that the prince said it was so.

214
00:29:57,240 --> 00:30:00,040
那晚王子一直没入睡
The prince never fell asleep that night...

215
00:30:00,990 --> 00:30:04,540
却等着农夫的女儿沉眠于睡梦中
but waited for the farmer's daughter to be lost in her dreams...

216
00:30:05,060 --> 00:30:08,010
然后展开了他真正的计划
and then began his real plan.

217
00:30:09,390 --> 00:30:10,180
什么
What?

218
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:16,900
他知道她的死会引发完全毁灭女王的星星之火
He knew her death would start a fire that would consume the queen entire.

219
00:30:21,940 --> 00:30:24,320
这故事太糟糕了 是骗人的
That's a terrible story. And a cheat.

220
00:30:24,320 --> 00:30:25,840
这是一个真实的故事
It's a true story.

221
00:30:25,850 --> 00:30:28,560
很多真实的事物都像是骗人的
Many things that are true feel like a cheat.

222
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:31,200
王国得到了值得拥有的王子
Kingdoms get their princes they deserve.

223
00:30:31,410 --> 00:30:33,730
农夫的女儿死于无辜
Farmers' daughters die for no reason.

224
00:30:33,970 --> 00:30:36,860
而有时候女巫又应该被救
And sometimes witches merit saving.

225
00:30:37,650 --> 00:30:40,480
你会觉得惊讶 实际上 经常有这种事
Quite often, actually. You'd be surprised.

226
00:30:42,870 --> 00:30:47,800
所以好王子是一个杀人犯 而邪恶的女王到最后却不是女巫?
So the good prince was a murderer and the evil queen was no witch after all?

227
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:51,640
女王当然是女巫
No, the queen was most certainly a witch...

228
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:55,110
也可能制造更大的邪恶
and could well have been on her way to great evil.

229
00:30:55,220 --> 00:30:56,780
谁知道呢
Who can say?

230
00:30:56,860 --> 00:30:58,420
那你为什么要救她
Then why did you save her then?

231
00:30:58,480 --> 00:31:02,410
因为她不是凶手
Because what she was not, was a murderer.

232
00:31:04,490 --> 00:31:06,440
她没给国王下毒
She hadn't poisoned the king.

233
00:31:06,830 --> 00:31:09,760
他只是年迈了
He had merely grown old.

234
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:12,770
王子有被抓起来吗
Did the prince ever get caught?

235
00:31:12,940 --> 00:31:15,890
没有 他成了一个受人爱戴的国王
No. He became a much beloved king...

236
00:31:16,590 --> 00:31:20,440
开心地统治着 直到死去
who ruled happily until the end of his long days.

237
00:31:20,530 --> 00:31:21,990
没错
Oh yes.

238
00:31:22,630 --> 00:31:23,920
我不明白
I don't get it.

239
00:31:24,570 --> 00:31:25,780
谁是好人呢
Who is the good guy here?

240
00:31:25,860 --> 00:31:28,790
不会一直有好人 康纳·奥马利...
There is not always a good guy, Conor O'Malley...

241
00:31:28,830 --> 00:31:30,920
也不会一直有坏人
nor is there always a bad one.

242
00:31:30,940 --> 00:31:33,460
很多人都介于这两者之间
Most people are somewhere in between.

243
00:31:35,270 --> 00:31:38,080
这些怎么从外婆那把我救出来
So how is this all meant to save me from grandma?

244
00:31:39,700 --> 00:31:42,960
不是从她那把你救出来
It is not her you need saving from.

245
00:32:02,900 --> 00:32:04,740
故事总有两面性
There are always two sides to a story.

246
00:32:04,900 --> 00:32:07,270
你们有多少人知道一句俗话
Now, how many of you know the saying:

247
00:32:07,270 --> 00:32:12,860
棍棒和石头可能会打断我的骨头 但言词永远伤害不了我
"Stick and stones may break my bones, but words can never touch me?"

248
00:32:13,620 --> 00:32:16,340
这样的话 下次要有人对你们说了什么 只要记住...
That way the next time someone says something to you just remember...

249
00:32:41,710 --> 00:32:43,480
很好 你到家了
Good, you're home.

250
00:32:44,510 --> 00:32:46,800
你妈妈在楼上 她想和你谈谈
Your mum's upstairs. She wants to talk to you.

251
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:50,200
- 什么 - 你爸周日会坐飞机过来
- What? - Your father's flying in on Sunday.

252
00:32:50,730 --> 00:32:53,010
爸爸要来了? 从美国过来?
Dad's coming? From America?

253
00:32:53,890 --> 00:32:54,600
去吧
Go on.

254
00:32:55,360 --> 00:32:57,070
她等着呢
She's waiting.

255
00:32:57,730 --> 00:32:59,070
打包好你的东西
And pack your bag.

256
00:32:59,070 --> 00:33:01,170
你要来和我住几天
You're coming to stay with me for a few days.

257
00:33:02,500 --> 00:33:03,520
去吧
Go on.

258
00:33:17,740 --> 00:33:19,740
那棵树很赞
That tree is amazing.

259
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:23,280
在这里矗立了数千年
It's been here for thousands of years.

260
00:33:26,290 --> 00:33:27,460
你觉得怎么样
What do you think?

261
00:33:28,650 --> 00:33:31,320
我觉得外婆想把我变成蒂娜·特纳
I think Grandma is trying to turn me into Tina Turner.

262
00:33:32,940 --> 00:33:34,240
她一定是她粉丝
She must be a fan.

263
00:33:39,320 --> 00:33:41,190
我为什么要和外婆住
Why am I going to stay with grandma?

264
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:46,970
你要回医院吗
Are you going back to the hospital?

265
00:33:49,240 --> 00:33:50,650
过来 康
Come here, Con.

266
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:59,000
上一次治疗没达到效果
This latest treatment is not doing what it's supposed to.

267
00:34:00,770 --> 00:34:02,530
所以要调整下
So they're going to adjust it...

268
00:34:03,410 --> 00:34:04,750
尝试别的
try something else.

269
00:34:07,410 --> 00:34:09,300
-  就这样? - 就这样
- That's all? - That's all.

270
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:12,020
你确定吗
Are you sure?

271
00:34:15,140 --> 00:34:16,680
确定
I'm sure.

272
00:34:18,280 --> 00:34:19,850
因为...
Because...

273
00:34:20,610 --> 00:34:22,230
你能跟我讲的
you can tell me, you know.

274
00:34:44,330 --> 00:34:46,190
一切都会好的 康纳
Everything will be fine, Conor.

275
00:34:48,070 --> 00:34:49,460
你会看到的
You'll see.

276
00:35:36,310 --> 00:35:38,190
等等我们 康纳 你要去哪
Wait for us, Conor. Where are you going?

277
00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:42,140
- 不要碰他  - 不要碰他?
- Don't touch him. - "Don't touch him?"

278
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:44,520
- 我给他脸上来一下怎么了 - 我说了别碰他
- With a punch to the face? - I said don't touch him.

279
00:35:47,260 --> 00:35:49,370
奥马利和我有共识
O'Malley and I have an understanding.

280
00:35:50,550 --> 00:35:52,440
我是唯一能碰他的人
I'm the only one who touches him.

281
00:35:53,610 --> 00:35:54,880
对吗
Isn't that right?

282
00:35:55,860 --> 00:35:56,980
告诉我
Now tell me.

283
00:35:58,910 --> 00:36:03,050
为什么每次我转过身 你就在那看着我
Why is it that every time I turn around, you're there looking at me?

284
00:36:03,540 --> 00:36:07,180
你不觉得很怪吗
Getting a bit odd, don't you think?

285
00:36:10,590 --> 00:36:11,940
抱歉 这有点残酷
Sorry, that was a bit harsh.

286
00:36:12,060 --> 00:36:14,260
今天 生活没能如你所愿 对吧
Life isn't really going your way today, is it?

287
00:36:33,890 --> 00:36:35,550
我要带人去看房子
I have a house to show.

288
00:36:35,950 --> 00:36:39,070
我相信你会一个人待在这里等你父亲
I trust you alone here till your father shows up.

289
00:36:39,270 --> 00:36:41,090
我现在不是五岁
I'm not five years old.

290
00:36:43,080 --> 00:36:44,700
这是正确的时间
This is the correct time.

291
00:36:44,890 --> 00:36:48,070
你手机 电脑上都不对
Not the one on your phone or on the computer,

292
00:36:48,270 --> 00:36:49,860
就连新闻上的也不对
not even on the news.

293
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:53,320
这是我母亲的 你曾外婆的
That was my mother's, your great grandmother's.

294
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:56,240
完美无误地走了一百多年
Perfect timekeeping for over a hundred years.

295
00:36:57,010 --> 00:36:59,240
康纳 过来收拾好
Conor! Pack up your rucksack.

296
00:37:01,260 --> 00:37:04,780
我不希望你父亲觉得我让你生活在猪圈里
I don't want your father to think that I'm keeping you in a pigsty.

297
00:37:05,280 --> 00:37:07,360
- 真是没什么机会 - 是的
- Not much shots of that. - No.

298
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:10,360
等你去了医院
When you go to the hospital,

299
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:13,120
你父亲可能不会注意到你母亲会有多累
your father may not notice how tired you mother's becoming.

300
00:37:13,120 --> 00:37:16,380
所以我们必须确保他不会待太久
So we have to make sure he does not overstay his welcome.

301
00:37:16,780 --> 00:37:19,090
这跟以前的事无关
Not that that's been a historically problem.

302
00:37:19,890 --> 00:37:22,800
不能吃鸡蛋 这周你已经吃过两次了
No eggs. You already had eggs twice this week.

303
00:37:23,090 --> 00:37:24,510
如果你饿了
If you are getting hungry,

304
00:37:24,710 --> 00:37:27,170
冰箱里有菠菜你可以蒸
there is spinach in the fridge you can steam.

305
00:37:27,300 --> 00:37:29,240
当然
Yeah, sure.

306
00:37:29,410 --> 00:37:30,790
什么都别碰
Don't touch anything.

307
00:37:33,330 --> 00:37:35,880
我会尽最大努力什么都不碰的
I will do my very best not to.

308
00:38:10,970 --> 00:38:11,910
找到了
Get it.

309
00:39:45,810 --> 00:39:46,550
爸爸
Dad.

310
00:40:25,610 --> 00:40:27,430
你怎么样 康 你看上去很累
How are you doing, Con? You look tired.

311
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:28,720
我挺好
I'm fine.

312
00:40:29,260 --> 00:40:31,720
妈妈在用新药 会让她好转
Mum's on this new medicine. And it will make her better.

313
00:40:32,220 --> 00:40:34,770
她每两个星期去次医院
She goes to the hospital every two weeks...

314
00:40:34,930 --> 00:40:39,810
他们把药物打入她的血流
and they pump the medicine into her bloodstream.

315
00:40:39,970 --> 00:40:43,740
她会发病几天 然后好转
She's sick for the next few days, but she's better again.

316
00:40:50,720 --> 00:40:55,380
- 你妹妹最近挺好  - 同父异母的妹妹
- Your sister is doing better. - Half sister.

317
00:40:56,350 --> 00:40:57,510
是的
Yeah.

318
00:40:57,680 --> 00:40:59,600
我想让你和她见见
I'd still love you to meet her.

319
00:41:01,050 --> 00:41:04,100
我跟你外婆谈过了 想把你带去洛杉矶
I've been talking with your grandmother about bringing you out to LA.

320
00:41:04,970 --> 00:41:07,820
- 你想让我去洛杉矶? - 是的
- You want me to come to LA? - Yeah absolutely.

321
00:41:07,890 --> 00:41:10,250
- 你想去的吧 - 是的
- You'd like that wouldn't you? - Yeah.

322
00:41:10,310 --> 00:41:11,590
我们去那过圣诞
We were thinking over Christmas,

323
00:41:11,660 --> 00:41:13,580
回来正好能上学
that way you can be back here in time for school.

324
00:41:15,650 --> 00:41:17,410
你意思是去玩咯
So you mean just for a visit then?

325
00:41:17,610 --> 00:41:19,260
对啊 会很棒
Yeah, but it would be great.

326
00:41:20,190 --> 00:41:22,090
我不想和外婆住
I don't want to live with grandma.

327
00:41:22,290 --> 00:41:24,960
那是个老女人的房子 里面全是老女人的东西
It's an old lady's house with old ladies' things.

328
00:41:25,020 --> 00:41:26,870
你什么都不能碰 哪里都不能坐
Can't touch anything or sit anywhere.

329
00:41:27,070 --> 00:41:29,280
连胡闹两秒钟都不行
Can't even leave a mess for two seconds.

330
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:30,140
康纳 我知道 但...
Conor, I know, but...

331
00:41:30,150 --> 00:41:33,320
我想要自己房子的房间 自己的东西
I want to have my own room in my my own house with my own things.

332
00:41:33,420 --> 00:41:34,990
你来美国也不会有啊 康纳
Well, you wouldn't have that in America, Conor.

333
00:41:34,990 --> 00:41:36,260
几乎没足够空间给我们三个了
There is barely enough room for the three of us.

334
00:41:36,260 --> 00:41:37,970
- 我不管  - 康纳 听着...
- I do not care. - Conor listen...

335
00:41:37,970 --> 00:41:40,270
- 她太严厉了 - 你的家人 你的生活 你的朋友...
- She's so strict. - Your family, your life, your friends...

336
00:41:40,430 --> 00:41:44,140
- 她家像个博物馆 - 你的学校 一切都在这里 好吗
- Her house is like a museum. - Your school, all of it is here, okay?

337
00:41:44,310 --> 00:41:45,990
把你带离这里是不公平的
It would be unfair to take you out of here.

338
00:41:46,140 --> 00:41:47,920
- 对谁不公平 - 康纳
- Unfair to whom? - Conor.

339
00:41:59,550 --> 00:42:02,390
你外婆好像还没回家
Doesn't look like your grandmother's home yet.

340
00:42:03,190 --> 00:42:06,550
她有时会在我睡觉后再回医院去
She sometimes goes back to the hospital after I go to bed.

341
00:42:06,720 --> 00:42:09,220
护士让她睡在一张椅子上
The nurses let her sleep in a chair.

342
00:42:09,390 --> 00:42:12,090
你外婆不喜欢我
Hey, just because your grandmother

343
00:42:12,090 --> 00:42:13,540
不代表她是个坏人
doesn't like me, doesn't make her a bad person.

344
00:42:13,540 --> 00:42:15,310
她说你总有始无终
She says you're all start and no finish.

345
00:42:17,810 --> 00:42:20,810
她有权表达她自己的看法
Well, she entitled to her own opinion.

346
00:42:22,310 --> 00:42:24,140
你会待多久
How long are you here for?

347
00:42:24,310 --> 00:42:26,970
能多久就多久
